Problem Description
You are managing a specialized service elevator that can only transport one person at a time.
People arrive at the elevator lobby to either enter the elevator to go up or exit the elevator to leave.
Because the space is narrow, if multiple people are waiting, the system follows specific priority rules
based on the elevator's "momentum" to determine who moves next.
Priority Rules
● Momentum Rule: If the elevator was used in the previous second, the person moving in the
same direction as the last user gets preference.
● Idle Rule: If the elevator was not used in the previous second (it was idle), the exiting (1)
direction gets preference over the entering (0) direction.
● Solitary Rule: If only one direction has people waiting at the current time, that person goes
immediately, regardless of the previous state or the idle rule.
This is a simulation problem. To solve it efficiently, maintain two separate queues—one for entering
(0) and one for exiting (1)—containing (original_index, arrival_time) pairs.




Sample Test Case 1
Input:
0 0 1 5
0 1 1 0
Output:
2 0 1 5
Sample Test Case 2
Input:
0 1 1 3 3
0 1 0 0 1
Output:
0 2 1 4 3
Explanation for test case 1:
● At t=0: Person 0 (Enter) and Person 1
(Exit) arrive. Elevator was idle, so Exit
gets priority. Person 1 goes at t=0.
● At t=1: Person 2 (Exit) arrives. Since
the last move was an Exit, the
Momentum Rule gives Person 2
priority. Person 2 goes at t=1.
● At t=2: Only Person 0 (Enter) is left.
They go at t=2.
● At t=5: Person 3 (Enter) arrives and
goes immediately at t=5




SOlution:-
#include<stdio.h>
#include<stdlib.h>
#include<string.h>
#define MAX 1000
int main(){
    printf("Hello World!\n");
    int n;
    printf("Please enter the number of people who will arrive: ");
    scanf("%d", &n);
    int time[n];
    int dir[n];
    for(int i = 0; i<n; i++){
        printf("Please enter the arrival time of person %d: ", i+1);
        scanf("%d", &time[i]);
        printf("Please enter the direction of travel(0:enter, 1:exit) of person %d: ", i+1);
        scanf("%d", &dir[i]);
    }
    int enter[MAX];
    int exit[MAX];
    int ef = 0;
    int er = -1;
    int xf = 0;
    int xr = -1;
    
    int ans[n];
    int t = 0;
    int i = 0;
    int last = -1;
    
    while(i<n || ef <= er || xf<= xr){
        while(i<n && time[i] <= t){
            if(dir[i] == 0){
                enter[++er] = i;
            }
            else{
                exit[++xr] = i;
            }
            i++;
        }
        if (ef <= er && xf <= xr) {
            if (last == -1) {
                ans[exit[xf]] = t;
                xf++;
                last = 1;
            } else if (last == 1) {
                ans[exit[xf]] = t;
                xf++;
            } else {
                ans[enter[ef]] = t;
                ef++;
                last = 0;
            }
            t++;
        } 
        else if (xf <= xr) {
            ans[exit[xf]] = t;
            xf++;
            last = 1;
            t++;
        } 
        else if (ef <= er) {
            ans[enter[ef]] = t;
            ef++;
            last = 0;
            t++;
        } 
        else {
            t = time[i];
            last = -1;
        }
    }
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        printf("%d ", ans[i]);
    }
    return 0;
}
